Great choice! Let's build an **Expense Tracker App** step by step using **React + Bootstrap**. This project will help you practice:

- React state management
- Form handling
- List rendering
- Calculating totals
- Optional: localStorage for persistence

---

## ‚úÖ Features We'll Build

1. Add expense (description, amount, type)
2. List of expenses
3. Show **total income**, **total expense**, and **balance**
4. Optional: delete an entry
5. Optional: save to localStorage

---

## üîß Step-by-Step Plan

### üîπ Step 1: Project Setup

1. **Create React App** (if not already):

```bash
npx create-react-app expense-tracker
cd expense-tracker
npm install bootstrap
```

2. **Import Bootstrap in `index.js`:**

```js
import "bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css";
```

---

### üîπ Step 2: Basic Structure

We'll build three components:

- `ExpenseForm` ‚Äì to add expense
- `ExpenseList` ‚Äì to show expenses
- `Summary` ‚Äì to show income/expense/balance

Here‚Äôs the file structure:

```
src/
  components/
    ExpenseForm.jsx
    ExpenseList.jsx
    Summary.jsx
  App.js
```

---

## ‚ú® Step 3: `App.js` ‚Äì Main App Component

```jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import ExpenseForm from "./components/ExpenseForm";
import ExpenseList from "./components/ExpenseList";
import Summary from "./components/Summary";

function App() {
  const [expenses, setExpenses] = useState([]);

  const addExpense = (expense) => {
    setExpenses([...expenses, expense]);
  };

  return (
    <div className="container mt-5">
      <h2 className="text-center mb-4">Expense Tracker</h2>
      <Summary expenses={expenses} />
      <ExpenseForm onAdd={addExpense} />
      <ExpenseList expenses={expenses} />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

---

## üßæ Step 4: `ExpenseForm.jsx`

```jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";

const ExpenseForm = ({ onAdd }) => {
  const [desc, setDesc] = useState("");
  const [amount, setAmount] = useState("");
  const [type, setType] = useState("expense");

  const handleSubmit = (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (!desc || !amount) return;

    onAdd({
      id: Date.now(),
      desc,
      amount: parseFloat(amount),
      type,
    });

    // Clear form
    setDesc("");
    setAmount("");
    setType("expense");
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="mb-4">
      <div className="row g-2">
        <div className="col-md-5">
          <input
            type="text"
            className="form-control"
            placeholder="Description"
            value={desc}
            onChange={(e) => setDesc(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>
        <div className="col-md-3">
          <input
            type="number"
            className="form-control"
            placeholder="Amount"
            value={amount}
            onChange={(e) => setAmount(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>
        <div className="col-md-2">
          <select
            className="form-select"
            value={type}
            onChange={(e) => setType(e.target.value)}
          >
            <option value="expense">Expense</option>
            <option value="income">Income</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div className="col-md-2">
          <button className="btn btn-primary w-100" type="submit">
            Add
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </form>
  );
};

export default ExpenseForm;
```

---

## üìÉ Step 5: `ExpenseList.jsx`

```jsx
import React from "react";

const ExpenseList = ({ expenses }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h5>Transactions</h5>
      <ul className="list-group">
        {expenses.map((exp) => (
          <li
            key={exp.id}
            className={`list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center ${
              exp.type === "income"
                ? "list-group-item-success"
                : "list-group-item-danger"
            }`}
          >
            {exp.desc}
            <span>
              {exp.type === "income" ? "+" : "-"}‚Çπ{exp.amount}
            </span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
};

export default ExpenseList;
```

---

## üìä Step 6: `Summary.jsx`

```jsx
import React from "react";

const Summary = ({ expenses }) => {
  const income = expenses
    .filter((e) => e.type === "income")
    .reduce((sum, e) => sum + e.amount, 0);

  const expense = expenses
    .filter((e) => e.type === "expense")
    .reduce((sum, e) => sum + e.amount, 0);

  const balance = income - expense;

  return (
    <div className="mb-4 p-3 border rounded bg-light">
      <h4>Summary</h4>
      <p>Income: ‚Çπ{income}</p>
      <p>Expense: ‚Çπ{expense}</p>
      <h5>Balance: ‚Çπ{balance}</h5>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Summary;
```

---

